annotation.TEXT: Ah, there we go, and he spit out a couple of little koopduders.
Just missed it. I'll try again.
Wow, I think I got lucky with dodging those fireballs there!
So, how long are you gonna stay spinning?
And there's another silly face, on its side and with its tongue sticking out.
Oh, am I done?
Oh, wait. There's a > next to it, so maybe this is greater than 2013! So... 2014, right?
Oh, man. That unlocked The Last Castle! But, I doubt I'll be headed there next. So, what's beyond the pipe after Yobigshi?
Okay, I should totally be able to make this jump.
...Aaany day now...
Woo! Good thing I didn't waste my double jump too early there! Also, that line-guide shape looks sort of like a mushroom.
Alright, the second half begins with me going under a pillar. Please don't headbonk the underside of the pillar. That would be bad.
Pac-Man's mouth looks a little off, though... I wonder if that's due to line-guide limitations.
Just checking something real quick there. (No, it doesn't look like there's anything solid close to the line-guided ropes for me to do the climb-on-air glitch with.)
Aaand... We're doing this again.
Whoa, they did that twice in a row, but at least I had plenty of time to react.
Hello, and welcome back to Something else! So, will the next level I play be Maximum Athletic 2?
Also, which power up should I use? I guess I'll jump on both of them at once and let the game decide.
So, place your votes for either The Last Castle, Spikitu Castle 2 *, or Bullet Bird Boom, and we'll find out where I'm going next time! To be continued...
Whoa, man! >=3
That looks like a flower... maybe.
Umm... Okay, are you gonna stop spinning around any day now?
Ooh, just made that one, too!
Or, will it be Boss - Yobigshi? Let's find out!
Moon count: 19 1-ups earned this time: 15.05. Bonus game average so far: 121.97 / 14 = 8.71214 1-ups each.

There's a goal point that doesn't work, because the goal tape is missing (probably intentional, since the level just started), and a left arrow and an I♥U sign with a pop-up 1-up hidden near it. So, I guess I gotta go left.
Well, I♥U too!
Whoa, so many squares! It's so hypnotizing! ...Actually, this looks almost like a teleporter from VVVVVV, except it's much larger, and doesn't warp me places.
Aw, that's cute.
Oh, man. An ON/OFF switch. It's probably going to alter the guide-line that the next platform is going around.
Spikitu Castle 2 *, and...
Goal tape average so far: 1630 / 48 = 33.958 stars each.
Oh, what? You're making me jump over munchers on top of pillars now? And I'm sure if I get bitten just once, I'm doomed. Also, since I can't land, I won't be able to refresh my double jump.
I guess I can't damage him while he's in this spinning pattern. (So, no rapid-hit cheesing like with Dedede in DDDark Castle.)
Oookaaay...
I don't suppose I can go up and over right here... Nope, thought not.

It doesn't look like I can wall jump off of the side of the stretching turn block bridge, though, so I've gotta be aware of that. Also, I see that 2013 there. So, maybe this level was made during that year?
R u ready?
DOUBLE KILL! Alright, finally!
There's the big guy alright, but that's no Yoshi! It's just a large version of one of those Yoshi-impersonating koopduders!

As for burning through 3 continues before a stage 1 midboss in a Touhou game, I think that can easily be accomplished in the regular Touhou games up to Touhou 8 by changing your starting lives to 1 in the options.
No custom music here? Well, there's a peach, which I was expecting. Also, there's a winged ? block to my left...
Wha-wha-wha-wha-wha!
Pokémon XD: Gale of Darkness?
NOTICE: I've removed the content ID matched audio from this point to about 6:41.
Alright, that unlocks this pipe on the right. But, before I check that out...
That smirky face has an upside-down ? for a nose. σ¿σ
That's odd how he shakes the ground as he jumps, and not as he lands. Shouldn't it be the other way around?
Bah, only 30... Come on, I should've been able to get at least 40 there... Oh, well. It's still enough for a bonus game.
Yeah, sprite platforms will usually let you stand on the edge of them while they're overlapping a solid wall like this.
It's not like this game has ignored too many laws of physics already...
Wait, there's four more ways I can scramble those syllables... Shiyobig, Bigshiyo, Yoshibig, and Bigyoshi... Wait, Big Yoshi?! Am I gonna have to fight a large version of my horse?
BGM: Sonic & Knuckles - Miniboss Battle
Luigi's number one!
Wah! Gotta be careful here. Good thing for the peach's unlimited wall jumping ability.

Yay! I won! Okay, that was a pretty interesting boss. It just needs to not occasionally spend forever in that boring spinning phase, and its stunquake timing should be adjusted to when he lands on the ground, so that it makes more sense.
Whoa, just made that one. Also, that duder I just passed had a nice 'stache.
Whelp, so much for that 1-up... Not that I needed it or anything.
Whoa! He's doing things again!
OOY
Wakka wakka wakka. Hey there, Pac-Man. How's it going?
M-M-M-MOOOOOOOONNNNSSSS!!!!
How did we not collide right there? Silly hitbox dissonance. I guess I've got to land squarely on the center of him to register a hit.
Huh, the next platform launches itself into the abyss fairly quickly, so I'd better be ready for that!
Aha! Yep, I was right! ^^
°A° ...Even in your Mario hack, F. O. E.!
...Bullet Bird Boom.
So, Shibigyo it is! Er, Yobigshi!
Yogui, you might want to adjust this boss so he doesn't remain in this spinning phase for so long.
Whoa! Hey, now! Don't you be dropping eggs on me!
Nothing up there, I don't think.
Athletic peach it is! Alright, it's boss time!
I think it's about time to take on Maximum Athletic 2! It shall remain taboo no more!
I'm liking these cute line-guide shapes, though. This level is really neat.
And then I let myself get OMNOMNOM-ed by the side munchers like an idiot...

Note: I received a vote for "Shibigyo - Boss" (which counts as Boss - Yobigshi, of course) after I had already recorded this episode, so there's actually 8 votes for Boss - Yobigshi. However, that doesn't change the outcome at all.
That shape almost looked like Yoshi.
What? Cheap! You all heard my jump sound effect as I got stunned there, right? Also, once again, I'll say that he should be causing his stunquakes as he's landing, not as he's leaving the ground.
